<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2834&amp;p=18943#p18943"><![CDATA[
You can change the size of the button from the Start Button tab in the settings. By default it is &quot;0&quot;, which means to use the actual size of the PNG file. Often times the button creators make a large image to preserve the quality at various sizes. In that case it is up to you to specify the size that works best for your taskbar. Try something like 40 or 50.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sun Apr 19, 2015 8:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
